**I. The End of Inequality**

*The world knew two kinds of businesses. The large — those who could afford consultants, auditors, strategists. The small — those left on their own. This divide was unjust. And we are ending it.*

For a century, the business world operated on the same model. Big firms arrived. Wrote reports. Collected fees. Left. The implementation was yours. The result was yours. The risk was yours.

McKinsey, Deloitte, KPMG, BCG — they all played the same game. They looked from above. Wrote reports. Sent invoices. And did they ever come down to the street level? No.

**The Infrastructure Argument**

A city cannot live without electricity. A city cannot live without internet. A city cannot live without water infrastructure.

*Why does a business live without Business Infrastructure?*

Why does it manage its finances in the dark? Why does human resources run on intuition? Why is operations written on paper? Why is strategy purchased from a consultant every five years? Because no one brought this infrastructure to them.

